## v16.9 - Do not use Flash, Active-X, Silverlight, NACL, client-side Java or other client side technologies not supported natively via W3C browser standards.

### Why is this required?

Several web technologies are vulnerable to attack and are becoming less supported by browsers.  Although there are several legacy web applications that still use many of these technologies, newer applications should use more secure technologies.

### Applicability (Level 1)

This objective applies to all apps.

### Guidelines for developers

Client side technologies must only include HTML, CSS, JavaScript (and associated libraries such as Angular or React), or VBScript
